# Spec Jedi hook-dispatch example (specs/050-reference-integrity-hooks)
#
# This is an INACTIVE TEMPLATE. Every specjedi-* pipeline skill that
# checks for hooks (specify, clarify, plan, tasks, implement, analyze,
# checklist, constitution, converge) only looks for a real
# `.specify/extensions.yml` at the repository root — this .example file
# is never read by any skill. To activate any entry below:
#
#   1. Copy this file to `.specify/extensions.yml` (drop the .example
#      suffix).
#   2. Uncomment (remove the leading `#`) only the hooks you actually
#      want active.
#   3. Nothing runs until you do both of those steps yourself.
#
# Every `command` below names a real, already-shipped specjedi-* skill
# in this project (dots become hyphens to form the real slash command,
# e.g. `specjedi.checklist` -> `/specjedi-checklist`, per every hook-
# aware skill's own documented Pre-flight/after-hook dispatch rule) —
# none of these are invented.

# hooks:
